Package <Unnamed>

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    FileSystem
    Your FileSystem implementation must create and manage a private disk and provide standard file system operations.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Bitwise
    Manage bitwise operations in a byte or array of bytes.
    DirectBlock
    Represents a direct block (block containing file data).
    FileTable
    Tracks open files and provides an interface to interact with files.
    FreeMap
    Provides the mechanism for interacting with bits in the free map, regardless of the block in which they reside.
    FreeMapBlock
    Stores 1 bit for each data block.
    IndirectBlock
    Indirect pointers from an Inode lead to an IndirectBlock.
    Inode
    Each file in your file system is described by an index node (Inode for short).
    InodeBlock
    Blocks on your disk which contain inodes are InodeBlocks.
    MyFileSystem
    Unit tests are in TestMyFileSystem.
    Shell
    Basic driver program to be used to test your FileSystem implementation.
    SuperBlock
    A disk block which stores information about a file system.
    TestBitwise
    Test the interface of Bitwise.
    TestMyFileSystem
    Test the interface of the file system and indirection.

    TestMyFileSystem.FreeMap  
    TestMyFileSystem.Indirection  
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Whence
    Determines the position from whence a seek operation should start.
